I think I know a bit more about what happened to you.  You went
looking for hosts BERKELEY.EDU and RICE.EDU.  Of course those
can't be host names (at least I think they can't) because they
are really domain names.  You ended up asking the BERKELEY.EDU
authority about the host BERKELEY.EDU.  It thought you wanted
the domain BERKELEY.EDU, and not unreasonably gave you information
on that domain.  You should be able to prevent this particular
loop by stopping your search for a host when it becomes clear
that it is really a domain.  I.e. the moment SRI-NIC told you
that BERKELEY.EDU was a domain, you should have stopped and
said "no such host".  At least that's my theory.
-------

